item.title: Toby add a quote by Groucho Marx
item.description: "I find television very educating. Every time somebody turns on the set, I go into the other room and read a book." -- Groucho Marx

item.title: Toby add a quote by Groucho Marx
item.description: "I sent the club a wire stating, PLEASE ACCEPT MY RESIGNATION. I DON'T WANT TO BELONG TO ANY CLUB THAT WILL ACCEPT ME AS A MEMBER." -- Groucho Marx

item.title: Toby add a quote by Groucho Marx
item.description: "One morning I shot an elephant in my pajamas. How he got in my pajamas I'll never know." -- Groucho Marx

item.title: Toby add a quote by Woody Allen
item.description: "I don't want to achieve immortality through my work; I want to achieve immortality through not dying. I don't want to live on in the hearts of my countrymen; I want to live on in my apartment." -- Woody Allen

item.title: Toby add a quote by Woody Allen
item.description: "I believe there is something out there watching us. Unfortunately, it's the government." -- Woody Allen

item.title: Toby add a quote by Woody Allen
item.description: "In California, they don't throw their garbage away - they make it into TV shows." -- Woody Allen

item.title: Toby add a quote by Woody Allen
item.description: "I hate reality but it's still the best place to get a good steak." -- Woody Allen

item.title: Toby add a quote by Jack Kerouac
item.description: "My fault, my failure, is not in the passions I have, but in my lack of control of them." -- Jack Kerouac

item.title: Toby add a quote by Jack Kerouac
item.description: "If critics say your work stinks it's because they want it to stink and they can make it stink by scaring you into conformity with their comfortable little standards. Standards so low that they can no longer be considered "dangerous" but set in place in their compartmental understandings." -- Jack Kerouac

item.title: Toby add a quote by Dennis Miller
item.description: "Jack Kerouac was cool because he had no idea he was." -- Dennis Miller

item.title: Toby add a quote by Robert Benchley
item.description: "There are two kinds of people in the world, those who believe there are two kinds of people in the world and those who don't." -- Robert Benchley

item.title: Toby add a quote by Robert Benchley
item.description: "Drawing on my fine command of the English language, I said nothing." -- Robert Benchley
